{
  "stem": "3341.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I-- in my teenage years, I can remember we had about six to eight people working, paid employees.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was a-- quite a good business.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I started school and I was five and a half or six years of age.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had only government schools.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were no private schools.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And also something which I can mention that we had-- I was born in the middle of Slovakia, which was, like, middle geographically.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was a strictly Slovakian area because Slovakia was bordered with Hungary, with Poland, and with Moravia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And each border line was influenced by the different languages of these parts.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Like, for instance, the Jewish people who were living close to the Hungarian border, their mother language, more or less, was Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were born-- or my family was in the middle of Slovakia, and we-- my mother language is Slovak.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We spoke Slovakian at home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "German I understood, but as a small child, I didn't speak German or Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you get used to the-- your ear gets used to it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But my parents were very advanced, I could say, because my mother couldn't manage the business and to look after the children.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they-- she engaged always a nanny for the children, which was a local girl.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But when we were already in the years of four or six, then we had a [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That is a-- a-- a children nanny, or how would you say that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she usually came from the German part of Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The German part of Czechoslovakia was up north at the Bohemia-- Sudetenland, which people--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--would have a idea of where it was.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
